<div class="shelff-hero">
  <img src="/shelff/shelff-icon.png" alt="shelff icon" class="app-icon" width="128" height="128">
  <h2>shelff</h2>
  <p class="tagline">A PDF reading app for iPad with no lock-in</p>
  <div class="cta-area">
    <a href="https://testflight.apple.com/join/GXQFQN44" class="cta-button">Try on TestFlight</a>
    <span class="pricing-note">The full release will be a paid app (one-time purchase)</span>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="shelff-features">
  <h3>Features</h3>

  <dl class="feature">
    <dt>Library</dt>
    <dd>Switch between grid view (large and small) and list view. Sort and filter to find what you want to read.</dd>
  </dl>

  <dl class="feature">
    <dt>Folders, Categories &amp; Tags</dt>
    <dd>Use your iCloud folder structure as-is. On top of that, organize freely with shelff's own categories and tags.</dd>
  </dl>

  <dl class="feature">
    <dt>Metadata Editing</dt>
    <dd>Edit title, author, publisher, language, description, and more. Automatic import of metadata embedded in PDF files is also supported.</dd>
  </dl>

  <h3>Your Data</h3>

  <dl class="feature">
    <dt>Everything Lives in iCloud</dt>
    <dd>Not just your PDF files — metadata and reading progress are also stored as JSON files in iCloud. If you're signed in with the same Apple ID, your reading progress and metadata sync automatically across devices.</dd>
  </dl>

  <dl class="feature">
    <dt>Open Metadata Format</dt>
    <dd>Metadata is stored as JSON files in iCloud in an openly specified, portable format. Other tools can read and write it alongside shelff.</dd>
  </dl>

  <dl class="feature">
    <dt>Organize your library with an AI Agent and the MCP Server</dt>
    <dd>On any Mac signed in with the same Apple ID, you can search and organize your PDF library using an AI agent and <a href="https://github.com/skoji/shelff-mcp/blob/main/README.md">shelff-mcp</a>.
    </dd>
  </dl>

  <div class="spec-link">
    <a href="<%= lang_path '/shelff/spec/' %>">shelff JSON Specification →</a>
  </div>
</section>
